  {
    "canonical_name": "Siyyid Ja‘far-i-Yazdí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Among them was a certain Siyyid Ja‘far-i-Yazdí, who in former days had exercised immense influence and had been greatly honoured by the people.",
      "He gave orders that the turban of that same man be befouled and flung into the fire."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1119, 1121]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí Muḥammad-Taqí (martyr of Nayríz)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Another victim of their tyranny was Ḥájí Muḥammad-Taqí, who had enjoyed, in days past, such a reputation for honesty and justice that his opinion was invariably regarded by the judges of the court as the determining word in their judgment."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1121]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "S̱hayḵh ‘Abdu’l-‘Alí (divine of Nayríz)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "S̱hayḵh ‘Abdu’l-‘Alí, who was Vaḥíd’s father-in-law and the leading divine of Nayríz, as well as a judge of great reputation."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1121]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Siyyid Ḥusayn (notable of Nayríz)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "together with Siyyid Ḥusayn, one of the notables of the town, were doomed to suffer the same fate. While they were exposed to the cold, the scum of the people was hired to heap upon their shivering bodies abominable cruelties."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1121]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Siyyid ‘Alíy-i-Zunúzí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "he was repeatedly urged, in view of the position which his stepfather, Siyyid ‘Alíy-i-Zunúzí, occupied, to recant his faith."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1138]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Báqir (mujtahid of Tabríz, son of Mírzá Aḥmad)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "From thence the Báb was conducted to the house of Mírzá Báqir, the son of Mírzá Aḥmad, to whom he had recently succeeded.",
      "My master is already satisfied that his father was right in pronouncing the sentence of death."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1140]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Aḥmad (mujtahid of Tabríz)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "the house of Mírzá Báqir, the son of Mírzá Aḥmad, to whom he had recently succeeded.",
      "My master is already satisfied that his father was right in pronouncing the sentence of death. He can do no better than follow his example."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1140]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Siyyid Muḥsin",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "He related all that he had seen to his neighbour, Mírzá Siyyid Muḥsin, one of the notables of Tabríz, who, as soon as he heard the story, was converted to the Faith.",
      "this same Mírzá Siyyid Muḥsin, who conducted me to the scene of the Báb’s martyrdom and showed me the wall where He had been suspended."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1147, 1148]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí ‘Alí-‘Askar",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "I have heard Ḥájí ‘Alí-‘Askar relate the following: “An official of the Russian consulate, to whom I was related, showed me that same sketch on the very day it was drawn.”"
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1155]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Yaḥyá Khán (father of Ḥájí Sulaymán Khán)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Ḥájí Sulaymán Ḵhán, son of Yaḥyá Ḵhán, arrived at Bág̱h-Mis̱hih, a suburb of Tabríz.",
      "The death of Farruḵh Ḵhán, son of Yaḥyá Ḵhán and brother of Ḥájí Sulaymán Ḵhán."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1156, 1234]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Sulaymán-i-Ḵhaṭíb",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "a Tablet He had revealed while in the neighbourhood of that shrine and which He delivered to a certain Mírzá Sulaymán-i-Ḵhaṭíb, who was instructed by Him to proceed together with a number of believers to that spot and to chant it within its precincts."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1158]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí Mírzá Jání",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Ḥájí Mírzá Jání, who had acquainted him with the precepts of the Faith.",
      "Ḥájí Mírzá Jání reported the matter to his Master, who charged him to assure the disgraced minister that ere long he would be summoned to Ṭihrán."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1160]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "the Niẓámu’l-Mulk (son of Mírzá Áqá Khán-i-Núrí)",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "His son, the Niẓámu’l-Mulk, one day asked him whether he did not think that Bahá’u’lláh… had failed to live up to the tradition of His father."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1162]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Ṣádiq Khán-i-Núrí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Three years after His martyrdom, that regiment mutinied, and its members were thereupon mercilessly shot by command of Mírzá Ṣádiq Ḵhán-i-Núrí."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1166]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Naẓar-‘Alí, the Ḥakím-Bás̱hí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "He shared his astonishment with Mírzá Naẓar-‘Alí, the Ḥakím-Bás̱hí, and recalled the glowing tribute which many a visitor to Zanján had paid to the abilities and integrity of the accused."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1175]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Raḥím-i-Zanjání",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "His father, Mullá Raḥím-i-Zanjání, was one of the leading mujtahids of Zanján, and was greatly esteemed for his piety, his learning and force of character."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1171]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Iskandar",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "he despatched his trusted messenger, Mullá Iskandar, to enquire into the claims of the new Revelation.",
      "as well as Mullá Iskandar and Mas̱hhadí Aḥmad, both of whom I sent to meet Him."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1173, 1192]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Qilíj Khán",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "A Kurd named Qilíj Ḵhán was commissioned by the S̱háh to deliver the royal summons to Ḥujjat."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1180, 1181]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḵhán-Muḥammad-i-Túb-C̱hí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "Ḥujjat had sent one of his friends, a certain Ḵhán-Muḥammad-i-Túb-C̱hí, to his Master with a petition in which he begged to be allowed to rescue Him from the hands of the enemy."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1180]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Ma‘ṣúm-i-Ṭabíb",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "the caravanserai of Mírzá Ma‘ṣúm-i-Ṭabíb, the father of Mírzá Muḥammad-‘Alíy-i-Ṭabíb.",
      "Mírzá Ma‘ṣúm, the former owner of the caravanserai, had lately died."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1185, 1186]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Muḥammad-‘Alíy-i-Ṭabíb",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "his eldest son, Mírzá Muḥammad-‘Alí, the leading physician of Hamadán, who, though not a believer, was a true lover of the Báb.",
      "The same night that witnessed my conversion."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1185, 1186, 1187]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mas̱hhadí Aḥmad",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": [
      "his special envoy, Mas̱hhadí Aḥmad, whom he had confidentially despatched to S̱híráz with a petition and gifts from him to the Báb, arrived at Zanján and delivered into his hands… a sealed letter from his Beloved."
    ],
    "mention_idxs": [1177, 1192]
  },
  {
